<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9543> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9543" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/10> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "ref. 300" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8684> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8684" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 747" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7001> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7001" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 92. Monetalis. In MRR 2.435, and Index, 547, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.313, no. 300, 110 or 109 B.C. Sumner notes that as his quaestorship is listed before the post of IIIvir monetalis in his inscription (ILS 45), Crawford's dating creates an unusually long, though not impossible date between the quaestorship and the consulship (ca. 110 to 92; Sumner, Orators 100-101). Cicero notes that he did not hold the higher offices suo anno (Off. 2.59; cf. 57). In a mistaken interpretation of Cic. Verr. 2.4.6, Drumann-Groebe (.2.156, no. 28) attributed to him a command in Sicily after his praetorship in 95. But the text shows only that he was a patron of Messana and hospes of the family of the Heii, from whom he borrowed, and returned promptly, an Eros of Praxiteles for his aedilician games in 99. An inscription of Cyrene honoring him  as patron when he was consul (#; see L. Gasperini, QAL 5; 1967, 53-57) is taken in AEpig. 1967, no. 532, to signify that he was proconsul there in 91 after his consulship, at a time before 75-74 when there was as yet no province of Cyrene. He was probably concerned with the lands bequeathed by Ptolemy Apion in 96 (J. M. Reynolds, JRS 61, 1971, 140; and JRS 52, 1962, 97-103, on the organization of the province). See Badian, Phoenix 25, 1971, 134-137.[57x]\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3780> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3780" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "CIL 11.2.663; Fast. Ant., Degrassi 164f., and Fast. Cap., ibid. 54f., 129, 480f.; Elogium, Inscr. Ital. 13.3.70b-CIL 12.1, p. 200; Obseq. 53; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Claudius, Cic. Cael. 33; Leg. 3.42; on Perperna, Val. Max. 8.13.4; Ascon. 28C; Plin. NH 7.156." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3776> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3776" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "8 The Elogium places this commission between the praetorship and the consulship of Claudius, therefore in 94 or 93." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3738> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3738" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Praetor (Cic. Verr. 2.2.122) in charge of cases of res repetundae (Inscr. Ital. 13.3.70b-CIL 12.1, p. 200). Commissioned by decree of the Senate, he drew up a constitution for Halaesa in Sicily (Cic. Verr. 2.2.122)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3695> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3695" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Had charge of the Quaestio de sicariis et veneficis (Elogium, Inscr. Ital. 13.3.70b-CIL 12.1, p. 200)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3694> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3694" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "3 Later practice, as in the case of Julius Caesar, who was Curule Aedile in 65 and Iudex Quaestionis in 64, favors placing the date, even in this early pre-Sullan instance, in the year after his aedileship (see 99, Aediles)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3671> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3671" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Inscr. Ital. 13.3, no. 70 b-CIL 12. 1, p. 200. Gave especially splendid games, and was the first to use elephants in venationes (Cic. Verr. 2.4.6 and 133; Har. Resp. 26; Off. 2.57; Val. Max. 2.4.6; Plin. NH 8.19, with the names of the Consuls; 35.23; cf. 21.6, where the praenomen is P.; Gran. Lic. 38 B)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3670> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3670" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "4 He was prosecuted by Appuleius Decianus after his aedileship, which should therefore be dated in 99." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3536> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3536" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See Mommsen, Ges. Schr. 7.517f., and the discussion in RE 1 A. 1273." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3535> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3535" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elogium, CIL 1\n     .1, p. 200- ILS 45." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3534> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3534" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Claudius apparently became a IIIvir Monetalis after his quaestorship, and his coins are usually dated about 104 (Mommsen, RMW 367; Grueber, CRRBM 1.198f.)." .
